headlines.description: — His right knee aching, Joel Embiid could have easily skipped a game against winless Detroit. As the 76ers watched another 20-point lead shrink to almost nothing down the stretch, Embiid instead got to work.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 30 on bad knee, 76ers hold off winless Pistons

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 27 points and Montrezl Harrell added 25 with 13 rebounds to lift the Washington Wizards to a 122-111 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Harrell lead Wizards over Hawks 122-111

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Kemba Walker scored 21 points, RJ Barrett added 20 and the New York Knicks hung on to hand the Chicago Bulls their first loss of the season, 104-103, on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker, Knicks hang on, deal Bulls first loss 104-103

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 19 points and seven Utah Jazz players reached double figures in a 122-91 win over the Houston Rockets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz put 7 in double figures as Utah routs Houston 122-91

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 10 of his game-high 25 points in the fourth quarter as the Dallas Mavericks beat the San Antonio Spurs 104-99 on Thursday night, after some wild swings in the first half before turning into a back-and-forth game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 25, Mavs beat Spurs 104-99 after wild swings

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — In his third NBA season, Ja Morant is speaking up during timeouts and showing his growth with every big basket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Memphis win a thriller on Curry's home court again
